<parameter name="content"># JuaConnect Backend Implementation Plan

## Database (PostgreSQL)
- User table with artisan/client profiles
- ServiceRequest table for bookings
- Booking table for scheduling
- Review table for ratings
- Payment table for transactions
- Notification table for alerts

## Authentication
- JWT-based authentication
- Secure password hashing
- Token refresh mechanism

## API Endpoints

### Auth Routes
- POST /auth/signup
- POST /auth/signin
- GET /auth/profile
- PUT /auth/profile
- POST /auth/logout

### Client Routes
- POST /client/requests (create service request)
- GET /client/requests (list my requests)
- GET /client/requests/<id> (get request details)
- PUT /client/requests/<id> (update/cancel)
- GET /client/bookings (list bookings)
- POST /client/book-artisan (direct booking)
- POST /client/bookings/<id>/pay (payment)
- POST /client/bookings/<id>/review (add review)

### Artisan Routes
- GET /artisan/profile (get profile)
- PUT /artisan/profile (update profile)
- GET /artisan/available-requests (browse requests)
- POST /artisan/requests/<id>/accept
- POST /artisan/requests/<id>/reject
- POST /artisan/requests/<id>/start
- POST /artisan/requests/<id>/complete
- GET /artisan/accepted-requests (my jobs)
- GET /artisan/reviews (my reviews)

### Search Routes
- GET /artisan/search (search artisans)
- GET /artisan/<id> (get artisan by ID)

### Notification Routes
- GET /notifications
- GET /notifications/unread
- PUT /notifications/<id>/read
- PUT /notifications/read-all
- DELETE /notifications/<id>

## Features to Implement
1. Real-time updates via WebSocket
2. M-Pesa payment integration (STK Push)
3. Image upload for profiles/portfolio
4. Email notifications
5. Admin panel routes
</parameter>
